<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910830-0026</DOCNO><DOCID>910830-0026.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- North Canadian Oils Ltd.:   Producer Agrees to Invest   In Two Cogeneration Plants</HL><DATE>08/30/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15</SO><CO>   NCD T.NCO</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>GAS UTILITIES (GAS)OIL-EQUIPMENT AND SERVICES (OIE)OIL-SECONDARY (OIS)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><NS>PETROLEUM MARKET (PET)</NS><RE>CANADA (CN)FLORIDA (FL)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   North Canadian Oils Ltd., Calgary, Alberta, said it agreedto invest up to $10.5 million in developing two electricalcogeneration plants in Florida.   The company said Peoples Cogeneration Co., a unit of LykesEnergy Inc. of Florida and the state's largest gas utility,will codevelop the projects and will provide the remaininghalf of the estimated $21 million of equity required. Thecompanies hope to complete arrangements for a $208 millionconstruction loan to build the two facilities by October.</LP><TEXT>   North Canadian said it will supply about 40 million cubicfeet of natural gas daily to fuel the projects when theybegin service in 1993.   It said the electrical energy produced by the projectswill be sold to Florida Power Corp. under a 20-year powerpurchase agreement and thermal energy produced will be soldto citrus processing concerns.   North Canadian is a Calgary-based oil and natural gasproducer.</TEXT></DOC>